    <briefdescription>
<para>Provides a thread-safe, singleton logger for writing trace information, warnings, and errors to registered listeners. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>The <ref refid="class_mandatory2_d_game_framework_1_1helper_1_1logger_1_1_logger" kindref="compound">Logger</ref> class does not add any default listeners. User must add one or more TraceListener instances using the <ref refid="class_mandatory2_d_game_framework_1_1helper_1_1logger_1_1_logger_1a543d8c665d9480d6c6c431ad5316a693" kindref="member">AddListener</ref> method to receive log output. This design allows the logging framework to remain neutral and adaptable to different logging targets. The singleton instance can be accessed via the <ref refid="class_mandatory2_d_game_framework_1_1helper_1_1logger_1_1_logger_1a63bb41f3132e391f305c2e4b17c2dd17" kindref="member">Log</ref> property.</para>
    </detaileddescription>
